			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">What's the use case?  I'm curious and I'd like to know what priority this should be.

&gt; Rather than failing in this case it should loop around to the beginning of the address space and start searching from there.

If we allocate at the start of address space we will prevent the brk() heap from expanding.  That might or might not be important.  An alternative is to search backwards; NaCl currently places mmap() allocations starting from the top of address space (below the initial stack).</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-03-13T20:32:24.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-03-13T20:32:24.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 1 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3341#c1" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3341/comments/full/1" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>